The paper deals with the problem of symmetric positive semidefinite (SPSD) matrix approximation, which has applications in kernel methods. This problem is related to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes new algorithms and provides theoretical analysis, which involves concepts from data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and signal processing (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NA and cs.LG, followed by cs.DS, cs.IT, and cs.SI.
